# I Know Kung Fu - Cursor IDE Rules

## Skill Loading

You have access to skill cartridges. Load patterns from skill-cartridges/ before complex tasks.

## Quick Reference

| Task | Load Skill |
|------|------------|
| File operations | skill-cartridges/document-operations/pdf-operations.json |
| Code generation | skill-cartridges/code-intelligence/code-generation.json |
| Reasoning | skill-cartridges/reasoning-patterns/react-reasoning.json |

## Key Patterns

### File Operations
- ALWAYS read before editing
- Use Edit over Write for existing files
- Never create files when editing suffices

### Code Generation
- Read codebase context first
- Follow existing patterns
- Generate complete, working code

### Reasoning
- Think → Act → Observe
- Iterate until complete
- Handle errors gracefully

## Forbidden Actions

- Never use cat/head/tail in bash - use Read tool
- Never use find/grep in bash - use Glob/Grep tools
- Never write without reading first
- Never create unnecessary abstractions

## Context Files

Always check for:
- CLAUDE.md in project root
- .cursorrules (this file)
- README.md for project context

## Performance

- Load skills proactively for complex tasks
- Use parallel tool calls when possible
- Track tasks with TodoWrite for 3+ steps
